cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.IR 

The paper discusses feature learning for object recognition using multidimensional scaling (MDS) applied on high-level pairwise image distances. This topic falls under computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The paper also discusses the use of semantics-sensitive image distances, which relates to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. Additionally, the experiments involve real images, which could be related to multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the performance of the MDS features for object recognition, which could be related to information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category.
